import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    # Calculate the difference between item size and bin capacities
    difference = item - bins

    # Divide the difference by the square of bin capacities
    divided_sizes = difference / (bins ** 2)

    # Calculate the scores as the reciprocal of divided_sizes
    scores = np.reciprocal(divided_sizes)

    # Sort the scores in descending order
    sorted_scores = np.sort(scores)[::-1]

    return scores
